   1. /shout in tox forest to see if anyone wants to group.<br>
   2. only kill things that are within sight of gaurds because you will need to run when the battle gets ruff.<br>
   3. go to Quenos and /shout if anyone wants to group cause there are ALWAYS alot of people  there.<br>
   4.in Quenos, look for warriors or tanks that are soloing there and ask if they want to group.<br>
   5.ask high level people if they can spare anything because usually they do and it is REALLY helpful<br>
   6.  one last thing.DONT hunt in tox forest cause it sux.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaisblackfingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/02 11:33:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: advice for young erudite mages</span><hr size=1> Yep- Erudites make some of the best mages (or any caster except 'chanter for that matter) b/c of the massive int.  Consequently, the newbie zone sucks.  The only way out is the boat, so take it, get yourself bound in Qeynos and don't look back for 20 levels at least.  Even then, only look back to buy spells in the library. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stina1701a>Stina 1701A</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/6/03 8:44:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: advice for young erudite mages</span><hr size=1> One other recommendation for young lowbie. Rats. Since the new armor quests the rats have gotten new drops besides the regular, ears, whiskers and meat and the occational foot. They have aquired the ability to see, in the guyse of an eye. Eye that goes for 2 gold apiece. Also the tail catches a hefty penny of a whole 1 plat. A nice catch for a youngling. Rats are not an isolated incident although the tail is the highest one ive found that sells for so much.<br>
<br>
Most dropped objects needed for the newbie quests and are not no drop go for about 2 to 4 gold appiece. and if they stack... whoopa mama!<br>
<br>
And I would also recommend doing the newbie armor quests themselves as well. It may be tedious getting all the items but the clothing is much more supperiour to banded or raw silk. Not only is it lighter; it is free. And most important, you get the pride of wearing something that you got for yourself. Through your own toil, determentation and ingeniouity you have gotten yourself a suit of armor and a weapon. And nothing can take that away from you.<br>
<br>
I experienced that with my young dwarven cleric. Got all pieces and the weapon. And I gotta tell you Im so proud im busting my bridges. But then again im NEVER going through that again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Stina 1701A<br>
